ps 
ps -a - shows only user define process start and stop 
ps -e shows all process in user and system 
ps -f full format info with detail
ps -elf  (all p)
ps -l long list 
ps -aux all process in wide format 
ppid parent process id
pid process id
NI nice (range is -20 to 20)
ps -axjf shows child process also tree diagram (x is to remove terminal)
sleep command used to frize system for some time ex sleep 30 system will sleep for 30sec
& sign will run process in background 
jobs command 


top command shows all process running as well as stop(real time process)
htop (it also shows full info)
running 
stopped
zombie
sleep
foreground and background process
nice value decides priority of process 
to search process id of process pidof sleep 
shows process id of sleep
to set priority of process we can use renice command 
renice -n -10 -p 5853   (-10 priority) (5853 process id )(n is number)
kill command use to delete process 
kill -l (to see the signal)
9 to force to stop
1 hang process 
15 to stop process 
Ex- kill -9 processid 
pkill -9 6328 process kill




